---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Job Processing System"
  subtitle="Background Job Orchestration"
  description="A distributed job processor with priority queues, DAG-based workflow orchestration, and multiple retry strategies."
  github="https://github.com/carissaayo/job-processing"
  tags={['NestJS', 'BullMQ', 'Redis', 'PostgreSQL', 'TypeORM', 'Docker']}
>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      A background job processing system built with NestJS and BullMQ. Jobs are persisted in
      PostgreSQL, queued in Redis via BullMQ, and processed by workers. The API and workers
      run as separate processes (or containers) and can scale horizontally.
    </p>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
      This project focuses on the hard problems in job processing: reliable delivery, priority
      scheduling, workflow orchestration, failure recovery, and operational visibility.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Architecture</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>API (NestJS)  →  JobsService  →  BullMQ (Redis)  →  Workers  →  Handlers
                       ↓                                           ↓
                 PostgreSQL  ←───────────────────────────────  Job results

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Priority Routing                                                   │
│                                                                     │
│  High (8-10)  ──→  high-priority queue   ──→  Worker Pool          │
│  Medium (5-7) ──→  medium-priority queue ──→  Worker Pool          │
│  Low (1-4)    ──→  low-priority queue    ──→  Worker Pool          │
│                                                                     │
│  Failed jobs  ──→  Dead Letter Queue (PostgreSQL)                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">Job Types</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="p-5 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-zinc-200 font-semibold mb-2">
          <code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">webhook.deliver</code>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          HTTP POST to a URL with idempotency key, HMAC signature, and timeout. Retries on
          5xx/429/408; fails fast on 4xx. Supports configurable retry strategies.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-zinc-200 font-semibold mb-2">
          <code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">report.generate</code>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Queries jobs by filters, exports CSV to disk. Optional webhook notification on
          completion for async report delivery.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-zinc-200 font-semibold mb-2">
          <code class="font-mono text-cyan-400">image.thumbnail</code>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Downloads image from URL, generates thumbnails using Sharp. Optional webhook
          notification on completion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Key Engineering Decisions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Separate API and Worker Processes</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          The API server and workers run as independent processes communicating through Redis.
          This allows scaling each independently: more API instances for higher ingestion throughput,
          more workers for higher processing throughput. In Docker, these are separate containers
          sharing the same Redis and PostgreSQL.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Multiple Retry Strategies</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Each job can specify its retry strategy: <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">exponential_backoff</code>
          (default), <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">fixed_delay</code>,
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">immediate</code>, or
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">circuit_breaker</code>. A
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">NonRetryableJobError</code> class allows
          handlers to skip retries for permanent failures (e.g., 404 from a webhook URL).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">DAG-based Workflow Orchestration</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Workflows define a directed acyclic graph of jobs with dependencies. Tree-shaped
          workflows use BullMQ's FlowProducer; fan-out DAGs use a custom orchestrator. Workflow
          creation is transactional (rollback on partial failure). Failed workflows can be
          resumed by retrying only the failed nodes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Dead Letter Queue with Resolution</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Jobs that exhaust retries or throw non-retryable errors are persisted in a PostgreSQL
          dead letter table. Each DLQ entry includes the full error history, original payload,
          and resolution status. Operators can resolve entries as retried, ignored, fixed, or
          deleted via the API.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Worker Crash Recovery</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          BullMQ's stall detection (<code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">lockDuration</code>,
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">stalledInterval</code>,
          <code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono text-sm">maxStalledCount</code>) automatically
          recovers jobs when a worker crashes mid-processing. Stalled jobs are re-queued up to a
          configurable limit before moving to the DLQ.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">API Endpoints</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Path</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/jobs</td>
            <td class="py-3">Create job (supports idempotency key)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/jobs</td>
            <td class="py-3">List jobs (filter by type, status, priority)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/jobs/:id</td>
            <td class="py-3">Get job details</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/jobs/:id/retry</td>
            <td class="py-3">Retry a failed job</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/jobs/:id/cancel</td>
            <td class="py-3">Cancel a pending/delayed job</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/dead-letters</td>
            <td class="py-3">List dead letter queue entries</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/workflows</td>
            <td class="py-3">Create a workflow (DAG of jobs)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">POST</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/workflows/:id/resume</td>
            <td class="py-3">Resume a failed workflow</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4"><span class="text-emerald-400 font-mono">GET</span></td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-zinc-300">/api/v1/monitoring/stats</td>
            <td class="py-3">System and queue statistics</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Project Structure</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>src/
├── modules/jobs/          # Controllers, services, handlers, DTOs
├── modules/workflows/     # DAG orchestration, FlowProducer, resume
├── modules/retry/         # Dead letter queue (list, get, resolve)
├── modules/monitoring/    # System and queue statistics
├── modules/audit/         # Job audit log (internal)
├── core/queue/            # BullMQ factory, worker bootstrap, processor registry
├── core/database/         # TypeORM, migrations
├── common/                # Guards (API key, rate limit), DTOs
└── config/                # Env validation, config</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
